# === notify: turn-ended audit backstop (config.toml-only surface) ========
# `notify` is NOT a hook event on codex 0.139 -- it is a top-level
# config.toml program invoked on turn-end notifications, so it CANNOT live
# in hooks.json. It is the audit chain's turn-level backstop (PLAN-155
# Wave 4-B): when per-tool-call appends were missed under partial
# interception, the turn-ended append (a DISTINCT registered action, so
# completeness analysis can tell the rails apart) still lands in the
# chain. Emission-only note: the distinct turn-ended action and the argv
# JSON ingestion path land with Wave 4; enable this line when Wave 4 is on
# main. The notify payload arrives as an ARGV JSON argument, not stdin.
#
# notify = ["bash", "{{PROJECT_PATH}}/.claude/hooks/_python-hook.sh", "audit_log.py", "--codex-notify"]
